09/11/2009
THE HAGUE, The Netherlands -- Macedonian Parliament Speaker Trajko Veljanoski has reassured former security official Johan Tarculovski that he can count on the support of Macedonian institutions in his appeal proceedings at The Hague war crimes tribunal, Veljanoski's office announced on Sunday (November 8th). He visited Tarculovski at the tribunal's Scheveningen detention centre. Tarculovski was sentenced last year to 12 years in prison for war crimes committed against ethnic Albanians during an August 2001 raid on the village of Ljuboten. His co-defendant, former Macedonian Interior Minister Ljube Boskovski, was acquitted. (Makfax, MIA, Sitel - 08/11/09)
